This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category as it focuses on training sparse neural networks using an evolutionary approach. The paper also proposes a novel approach to evolve the network topology based on the behavior of neurons, which is a common topic in the cs.NE sub-category.

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The proposed approach aims to reduce the storage and computational complexity of sparse neural networks, which is a common topic in the cs.LG sub-category.

The paper also involves artificial intelligence techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The proposed approach aims to evolve the network topology based on the behavior of neurons, which is a common topic in the cs.AI sub-category.

The paper also involves computer vision techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The experiments are performed on 8 datasets taken from various domains, including computer vision datasets such as CIFAR-10 and MNIST.

Finally, the paper involves control systems techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The proposed approach aims to evolve the network topology based on the behavior of neurons, which can be seen as a control problem
